// AlertsService — threshold-alert CRUD + recent-fires listing.
//
// An Alert is a persistent rule evaluated on a 1-minute ticker by the
// Phase-4 evaluator goroutine (pkg/alerts/evaluator). When a rule
// fires, the evaluator writes an AlertEvent row to Bolt, renders an
// email body, and hands it to pkg/mailer for delivery (reusing the
// Phase-3 mailer).
//
// Kinds (AlertKind):
//   GOAL_COUNT_ABOVE      — conversions for target_goal_id in the last
//                           window_minutes > threshold.
//   PAGE_TRAFFIC_DELTA    — pageviews to target_path in the current
//                           window_minutes vs the same window one
//                           week ago; fires when |delta_pct| > threshold.
//   FORM_SUBMISSION_RATE  — submissions to target_form_id per minute
//                           exceed threshold (spam burst detector).
//   BAD_ACTOR_RATE        — bad-actor hits/minute > threshold.
//   BUILD_FAILED          — any build_failed event in window (threshold
//                           ignored).
//
// Writes require server.<id>.admin; reads require
// server.<id>.analytics.read so non-admins can see the rules that
// govern the inbox they already receive.

